OL,3,CShoppers urged by Which? to consider
OL,4,Cprotections when using 'pay by bank'
OL,6,FUnder Section 75 of the Consumer
OL,7,FCredit Act, a credit card company can
OL,8,Fbe held jointly and severally liable
OL,9,Ffor a purchase that turns out to be
OL,10,Fshoddy or does not materialise, in
OL,11,Fcertain circumstances.
OL,13,FThis means that a shopper could
OL,14,Fpotentially get a refund from the
OL,15,Fcredit card company if they cannot
OL,16,Frecoup their costs from the retailer.
OL,18,FPeople using a debit card or a credit
OL,19,Fcard for purchases could also
OL,20,Fpotentially get their money back via
OL,21,Fthe voluntary chargeback scheme.
